VThese headphones have been lifesavers. Specifically, for my neighbor's dog's life.New neighbors moved into the apartment above mine, and they have two of those annoying little yippy dogs.  Whenever they leave, the dogs bark and howl and whine on a near-continuous basis.  Of course, the neighbors care nothing for anyone around them, the apartment complex just wants the rent money and nothing else, and the police have better things to do than respond to noise complaints.While coming here to Amazon to order a copy of Office Space to find tips on burning down the building with the yippy dogs inside, I decided perhaps rather than desperately turning to a life of crime, perhaps devices where available to stop the dogs from making my life a living hell.  Well I still have to go to work, but other than that, these Bose Headphones have proven to be a magnificent solution.  I put them on, plug them into my mp3 player, turn them on... and while the dogs can still be faintly heard, it is as if they were three or four apartments down, rather than right on the other side of the thin drywall.  I can live with that, and so can the dogs.That the headphones also do a great job at blocking out other noises like the dishwasher or the fans, is a wonderful bonus.  That they work with readily available common sized batteries is also fantastic.Thus, these headphones have saved two dogs' lives.  And perhaps the neighbors as well.  Maybe even kept me out of jail for 20  years.  They might seem expensive, but cheaper than a defense lawyer.
