VThe noise isolation is something out of this world. On par after reading all the reviews, and met my expectations. The sound itself nearly as bad as anyone would say it was on head-fi, I think they're just a bunch of audiophiles. When you turn the canceling feature off, the sound gets bad. I wouldn't know what a "high" or a "low" is, but they sound FANTASTIC to me. I've tried so many audiophile headphones and they're BETTER than some audiophile headphones I own. The noise isolation alone is already worth it.. kinda awesome sitting in a noisy place and not hearing the car move while it's driving when I'm on a trip with family.It doesn't necessarily CANCEL noise, it just turns down the volume in life by about 60-80 percent. Any fans, computers, cars, airplanes, trains... motor noises... it all cancels out by about 80 percent. Which can be a bad thing if you're walking on the street with these. I always like to keep a fresh energizer battery in it. When the light starts blinking, I change the battery out because the noise cancel feature suffers when it gets to that point. They truly are phenomenal.. I cannot recommend these enough. They're also some of the most comfortable headphones I've ever owned.Edit: They broke within a week, popping sound in right headphone. The wire is broken and cutting out. Im very unsatisfied with the quality of the construction on these.
