VFirst, I must say that I am a freak of nature in that I am not a big Bose fan or Apple for that matter. Having said that, I was looking for a set of noise canceling over ear headphones. I did much investigating in this area. What I found was NC from many brands was so so and not very reliable as many reviews said the NC stopped working in as little as a day and up to a year. The reviews of Bose QC products never indicated these type problems. I also quickly became aware that Bose dominates NC technology arenas not only in consumer products but industrial and military applications as well. Again, I never thought I would ever be buying a Bose product. Bose and Apple are full of proprietary issues from cables to you name it. So i bit the bullet and bought these QC25. I have not the slightest regret. They are magnificent. I can now sit at my computer on my loft and not be inundated with sound from my wife watching TV with 5.1 just below me. I swear she has hearing deficiencies. Not only does the NC do a stellar job, I am at this moment listening to the new Pink Floyd album on Spotify and it sounds great! Even when I am just perusing the internet with no audio source and just NC they attenuate the sound from downstairs so much that what ever she is watching is a mere whisper compared to sans QC25. I cannot say that I am a complete Bose convert but I damn sure am a QC believer! God bless all of the Bose and Apple fanatics. May they live long and prosper. We must all follow our own hearts. I heart my QC25. Yeah buddy!!!!
