VI received these as a gift which is why it doesn't show me as having bought them through Amazon. I am not an audiophile but even so I am pretty underwhelmed by the sound quality, especially for the price. The sound is just kind of flat, lifeless, and tinny. My twenty-dollar Sennheiser HD201 headphones sound much better to me. I had my wife compare the two headphones as well without telling her my opinion of them and she came to the same conclusion. The noise-reduction feature doesn't score any points with me either because it doesn't actually work that well. For all the added hassle of keeping a charged battery in the headphones and having to flip the little switch on the side, they barely block ambient noise better than the basic over-the-ear headphones I mentioned earlier.The two areas where these headphones do distinguish themselves are build quality and comfort. The build quality is flat-out awesome and luxurious, and they are definitely the best-built set of headphones I have used. They are also extremely comfortable-- so comfortable that I almost want to forgive them for the lousy sound quality. But not quite. Not for $300. Can't recommend these.
