VQC25s are 50 grams heavier and clamp stronger than QC 15s which significantly reduces comfort
p506
sg5
VI rarely if ever write reviews but I felt compelled to write this one as my opinion is quite different than most.  As it stands, the majority of reviews focus on sound quality and noise cancellation, I don't see there is much to discuss here especially in comparison to the QC 15 so I will focus on comfort which is my main concern and I believe it should be that of anyone wearing these headphone for long periods (travel, work and so on).  The QC 15 are definitely more comfortable, why? well for two main reasons: First they weight 145 grams as opposed to about 195 grams for the QC 25, this is a significant different, an increase of almost 33%.  Second the clamping mechanism is harder for the QC 25 which means you feel more pressure on your ears and skull, this makes them less comfortable if your head is above average in size.  It is worth noticing that my head is quite large yet I don't need to pull the retractable part by more than one tick which in my opinion indicates a design flaw for theses headphones.  Bottom line, value for money and in comparison to the QC 15, I regret buying them.
