VThe 25 is definitely better. The difference would not be very noticeable at first!
p597
sg5
VCompared to my Bose QC 15, this one is not worth the upgrade.Let us start with the GOODS: in terms of comfort and portability, the 25 is definitely better. The noise cancellation also improved slightly.As for the CONS: the new sound signature is not for me. I prefer the 15 over this one. The 25 has a higher bass emphasis which muffled the mids and highs. If you are a bass person, i guess this headphone is for you. If not, then look else where.If you want sound quality, check out Beoplay H6 or H8 (this one has Noise Cancellation).Update 08/2015: I bought this product again due to portable demands that my qc 15 could not offer. Of course, I got a good deal. After some burn in time, I compared the the 15 and 25 again. The 25 has better passive noise isolate and improved lower frequency noise cancellation (try it with the AC and you will see what I mean). In terms of sound quality, the bass of the 25 is still sloppy compared to other headphones I have like the Senheiser HD 598. The problem is I don't feel any punch from the 25. The bass on the HD 598 is a lot tighter. The vocals on the 25 is an improvement, probably because of the more emphasis on the higher-mids. Overall, I enjoyed this product and change my mind that this is worth an upgrade, eventhough the differences are not that noticeable at first. Give it some burn in time and you will be surprised.
