VI am a frequent flyer (6k-10k miles per month) and I formerly used Audio-Technica M50s. I realized that I was blasting the M50s at full volume to hear over the sound of flying and I know that can't be good for my ears. Furthermore, I started using a headphone amplifier to boost the lows which made them even louder.The noise cancelling is amazing. With the QC-25 headphones, I now find myself listening to my music/books/movies at a level that seems reasonable so that I hear every detail. The funny thing is when I take these off and realize how much louder the drone of the engines are than my music was. I end up unplugging the cord from them and wearing them to the airplane bathroom (13 hour flights) because they are so nice and quiet. I live in a quiet house, but these make me realize how not-quiet it is; if I take these off my house sounds like holding a sea-shell to your ear.The sound is great and they cover all ranges well. I haven't found advantage in using a headphone amplifier to boost the lows. In fact, I almost think that these have abnormal amounts of bass, but that is just personal taste.A word of advice: buy the Energizer Ultimate Lithium AAA batteries. They are pricey, but they are lighter and they last much longer so they end up being cheaper. I have at least 50+ hours on my first one.
