VWell designed, great noise cancellation, good sound quality
p1112
sg5
VThese are some very nice headphones.Pros:+ The noise cancellation feature is quite excellent. It's miles ahead of my other set of noise-canceling headphones (Sony MDRNC7/BLK). I can hardly hear outside noises when the headphones are activated. They do an admirable job of suppressing noises from airplane engines, open plan office spaces, and more.+ The headphones fit very nicely and are comfortable. I can wear them all day at my desk with no discomfort.+ The music sounds very good. For pure sound quality, I think I prefer my Sennheiser PC 310 Gaming Headset, but these Bose headphones aren't bad at all.+ The on-headphone buttons and microphone work great when plugged into my MacBook Pro. My Android Nexus 4 doesn't seem to recognize the microphone or volume buttons, but the center button works to pause and unpause music.+ For headphones as expensive as these, having the ability to replace the cable when necessary is a very nice touch. With the cable removed, these still work great to block outside noise, you (obviously) can't play any music in this mode though.+ The included case seems lightweight but sturdy. It has a slot for an extra battery and the airplane adapter: another nice touch.Cons:- When the noise cancellation feature is powered off, the sound quality drops off dramatically. For this reason I wouldn't want to use these headphones without an extra battery available.- The noise cancellation feature is really quite excellent. Other people in the same room have to make a special effort to get my attention when I am using these.- The price. I'm extremely grateful to have gotten a free pair of these headphones to review, but I doubt I would be willing to pay $300 for them.Overall, I think these headphones are a winner if noise cancellation is your primary concern. If you just want some amazing sound quality and don't need noise cancellation, you might have better luck with a different model.
