VProbably worth the cost.
p1158
sg5
VBACKGROUND:  I work from my home basement office  as a software developer, and was looking for something to help eliminate distractions from other sounds in the house: kids running around upstairs and making kid noises; clothes washers / dryers; the furnace; etc.EFFECTIVENESS:  When I first received these headphones I was a little disappointed with the efficacy of their noise-cancellation, considering their price and the glowing reviews from some sites that I trust.  This was my first impression from unboxing them and walking around the house, talking to people.  In particular, the headphones seemed far better at reducing mid/high frequencies than lower frequencies.  However, I was pleasantly surprised to find that when using them while I worked, the overall impact of the active cancellation is very effective, and I generally am no longer distracted by noises in the house.  In terms of audio quality for their basic headphone functionality, they're fine, about the same as I get from the Sennheiser headphones I bought about 15 years ago for $70.COMFORT AND AESTHETICS:  The headphones are lightweight and comfortable.  The headphones fit comfortably around my ears, and stay in place without being overly tight.  No complaints at all, except for having to deal with the audio cable(see below).FUNCTIONALITY:  The headphones have an inline volume controller and microphone, however these seem to only be effective if the headphones are plugged into an Android or iPhone.  (I haven't tried that feature on a phone; I've always used the adapter to simply plug them into my computer's standard stereo headphone jack.)WHAT I'D CHANGE:  For $300, it would be nice if the headphones had Bluetooth connectivity, for two reasons.  First, the audio wire is a bit annoying to work around.  Secondly, it would let the microphone work with any Bluetooth enabled device (such as laptops), rather than just with iPhones and Droid phones.CONCLUSION:  This being my only experience with noise-cancelling headphones, I'm not sure if the $300 price was necessary to get the quality of noise-cancellation I needed for my work.  But they work well, and let me do my job effectively and without distraction, and that's a pretty big deal.  Overall I'm happy with the purchase.
