p1164
sg5
VI travel quite a bit and have used a previous version of Bose headset which lasted a long time.What I Like:- They truly do drown-out the noises around you. Will it block out everything - absolutely not! Will they silent a baby sitting behind you and crying to an tolerable level, with a song on or a movie playing on your phone - yes! There is a reason why these headsets are frequently seen by business travelers. Before you take off for your next flight - glance around and count how many headsets you see on business travelers - can almost promise you will see 3-4 in clear site.- They look professional. Clean, elegant, simple. They come in a variety of colors and you can customize for additional money, but I stuck with the all black...just liked them.- Comfortable. I wear them sometimes for hours on end.What I Do NOT Like:- The genius who made the case that you put the headphones in somehow forgot to include a space for placing the cord to plug into your phone?!?!?!? Can't understand that little slip up. This dovetails right into point # 2 I don't like but I have gotten use to...- It takes AAA battery to operate. If you are like me and want to be sure you hear good sound or want to use the noise cancellation feature, then you will need to always carry an additional battery -or- be prepared to buy one in the airport, train station, wherever. Again, the genius who designed the carrying case forgot to include a compartment that holds additional batteries.**** I cannot think of a reason not to include a small little internal pouch that zippers inside the travel case for the headphones. This is truly unacceptable and flat out equates to either Bose thought about this and did not include it - which in my opinion makes me mad ... or Bose did not think about the typical traveler needing to store the cord and batteries when we travel with the headphones - which equates to stupidity. Either way, I'm not happy about it.Summary:Headphones work very well (they should for $300.oo USD). The travel case is stupid and doesn't contain a place to store an additional battery or the cord used to plug the headphones into your phone. All-in-all, I would buy the headphones again, just will need to now get a case that is frequent-traveler friendly.
