VThe QC25 is brilliant. I'm new to the world of ANC headphones, but I have used Beats before (which are sort of the runner ups) and they don't compare; price wise, as well as comfort and quality. First of all, the QC25 is the most comfortable headphones I've tried on. I even went to the local Best Buy and compared all the other NCs available like the Bowers, Seinheisser, Harmon & Kardon and Sony: the bose were absolutely the best fit for me. They're light, yet durable and they don't squeeze your ears which can be extremely headache-ing. They sit right over your ears. As I mentioned, the sound quality is exquisite. Now, it's not as ostentatious and loud as Monster or Skull Candy or even Beats, but the sounds that come out of the earphones are pristine, transparent, and crisp. You won't miss a single note or bass thump. The Acoustic Noise Cancellation is amazing... I bought these to silence my surroundings and they do just that. I can be in a cafe, a restaurant, or at a park and when I put these on I am alone with my computer or iphone. I can focus directly on my music and/or my project. I will say though, the ANCs sort give you the sensation that your eardrums are being sucked out, but I got used to it quickly. I'd like to think that it just adds to the legitimacy of the NC anyway.Basically those are the pros. Here are the cons: Not as loud as other wanna-be's. It is wired, BT would've been nice. Single AAA battery, instead of rechargeable lithiums. You won't get to hear your girlfriend when she says sweet nothings while you have these on, which is fine because you're listening to your music, but when you realize that her mouth is moving and she in fact is looking at you saying something with a smile on her face... you'd have to lift one phone up completely just to ask her what she said, but then she won't tell you because shes a girl and girls do that. Just sayin'.
