VWorks great (in the right environment)
p1366
sg5
Vthese work great--as long as your expectations are realistic. They are very good at canceling background sounds that are constant and even. Any sounds that are momentary come through loud and clear. I use these while driving a tractor which (due to the hydrostatic drive) runs at full RPM all the time. These headphones cut the engine sound by about 2/3. However, any other sounds are still just as loud (rocks being hit by mower deck, etc.) Listening to music is super clear, even in that loud environment. In fact, i'm hearing words in old songs more clearly than I ever have before... (Apparently, Benny and the Jets have electric "boots"...  Who knew?)My wife tried using these headphones while mowing lawn on a zero-turn mower. They did not do as well in that environment because the background sound changes so rapidly (engine sounds, hydraulic wheel drives, etc. are not smooth and even levels or pitches.) for that environment, she prefers to use drummer's headphones. Those don't have active noise cancellation, but they are better at passive isolation.I had a pair of bose noise canceling headphones about 5 years ago. I didn't like them--when active, they audio sensation felt like a kind of 'pressure' in my ears. This new model doesn't feel/sound anything like that. Much better technology.
