VA longtime audiophile, I've owned phones from the $100-$1000+ price range (AKG 701, Sennheiser 600, Beyer Dynamic T1 and Audeze LCD 2). While it would be unfair to expect the Bose QC 25 to deliver the detail, air or sound stage of the more expensive cans it does a surprisingly fine job of noise cancellation while delivering pleasing sound. Many audiophiles will dismiss the Bose line due to their market position and marketing budget. Some criticism is justified yet their noise cancellation line is almost universally recognized as without equal. Used these with my iPhone for the first time on a flight from NYC to Milan and was more than satisfied in the isolation. During the 3 weeks of travel on trains and the return trip the phones functioned on a single AAA battery - ~ 20 hours - another surprise. The battery survived a subsequent (3 hours each way) flight. I'm sure there is a spec on battery performance but it was a bit of a serendipity. While more expensive than their competitors it really delivers exceptional isolation coupled with very acceptable sound quality.  While I didn't compare with the others I did extensive research and chose this over brands I trusted and with which I had prior experience.
