VI bought these the other day and really like them. Their sound is good and everything is ...
p1797
sg5
VI bought these the other day and really like them. Their sound is good and everything is great but I'll cut to the chase:I wanted the in-ear version (QC20) but I have a cat who loves to chew through wires. In this version, the wire that connects to your device/headphone is detachable so that if a cat chews through it or it breaks you can just get a new one.Also, this version uses a AAA battery which means, ultimately, you don't have to worry about a non-replaceable battery going bad after a few years.I've used both and didn't really notice a sound quality difference.UPDATE January 2016:After two years of regular use, the left speaker stopped working. Very frustrating, since my product was out of warranty and I wouldn't expect this from a Bose product. I went to a Bose store to see what my options were and the lady working there said this headset has a known issue where it can fail and, regardless of warranty status, they are to do an exchange free of charge.So, I have a new pair of headphones, with a new warranty.Excellent customer service.
