VNot what I was expecting...
p1955
sg5
VI ordered these hoping the QC-25's were an improvement over the QC-15's I currently own. Don't get me wrong, I really like my QC-15's, I was hoping a 6 year refresh of this model would bring improvements. Overall, this was not the case. The non-battery sound quality is lack luster and the sound quality when running with Noise Cancelling on doesn't have the clarity of the QC 15's. Noise cancelling on the QC-25's are a bit better but not by much. These headphones, like most products these days, are targeted toward Apple products and smartphones, Bose did away with the extra non-phone cable that was included in their QC-15 Special edition earlier this year. Though it works fine with a standard MP3 player, the cord is shorter than previous versions and you are stuck with an inline Volume/Mic controller. And as per usual the controller has more functions with Apple products than Android. The QC-15's are the best Headphones I have ever owned. I have not found anything that comes close. I might by another pair of QC-15's before they go out of stock. Let's hope that Bose refines the QC-25's performance and features. They definitely didn't do their best on this release.
