VOnly One Problem
p2235
sg5
VGood noise reduction. Very light and comfortable. Perfect clamping force. Portable and well built. Highs are just right, smooth, clear. Mids are good except in lower mids. More on that later. The bass is nearly perfect. Extended, big, not boomy. There is a low mid issue. That rings about inside the cup, for a sometimes boxy sound. There needs to be more and better damping in there to prevent that. With or without noise canceling on, this happens. Noise cancelling makes the sound worse (it's harsh and artificial). It's better off, which defeats the purpose of these headphones. Keep working on it.
