VSixth Bose Product But Had To Return
p2781
sg5
VI really am sold on most everything Bose that I've bought over the last ten years.  I recently got the Bose SoundTrue and love them.  I paid substantially more ($290) for the Bose QC25 and loved the comfort, audio sound, and build quality.  But for the past month or so, I have to take them off after a half hour or so as the pressure on my eardrum starts to get a bit painful.  I know Bose says it really isn't pressure, per se, but I do feel it like some others do.  Most people do not have this problem.  After I don't use them for the rest of the day, my ears recover.  I try the next day and they start the pressure again.  Some of the electronics magazines say that is why Bose has a  30 day return policy.  My retailer gives me 90 days to return them even if they have been opened.  Since I got them, I've read that unless you are really going to use them for what they were designed for (airplanes, trains, office noise) they may be of limited use in your house and might not be worth having if noise-canceling is not a major concern.  I thought everything about these were great, but the pressure was just too much.  I figure at my age, 68, I don't need anything that might accelerate any hearing loss so I will be returning these before the 90 day limit.  My other Bose products (SoundDock, In-The-Ear headphones, and SoundTrue) I would rate tops as is Bose Customer Service.  I have found that by adjusting the EQ in iTunes, I can make my SoundTrues, In-Ear, and my Klipsch Status all sound better.  I hope others don't have this problem, though some do.  These are a 5 star product; but for me I have to give it 4 stars as they just don't work for me.
