VThe QC 25's are very comfortable, light weight
p2954
sg5
VAlthough we are not frequent fliers, we do make about one long trip per year, often to Europe, and the engine noise is stressful and very tiring. A friend on a recent flight had a pair of Bose QC 15's, which she raved about since she was in the military and made countless flights. I decided to take the plunge despite the very high cost. The QC 25's are very comfortable, light weight, fit snuggly over the ears and come with a very sturdy and compact carrying case. Tried them out with our riding lawn mower. The lower frequency roaring was effectively cancelled out and the higher frequencies reduced considerably. These are much, much more effective than both ear plugs and headphones. And I could listen to my mp3 player at normal volume levels. We are very impressed. One can use an external player without the cancelling turned on (e.g. no or dead battery) but the sound quality is a bit muddier. Best to use the SC mode to provide great bass and clear, crisp highs. We bought a pair of QC 15's (discontinued by Bose) from Costco a week after buying the 25's. Same sound cancelling performance, similar comfort but slightly different fit on the head and somewhat larger carrying case. And one must turn the sound cancelling on in order to use the phones with an external player.  We have been using the QCs now while mowing the lawn. We expect both will be worth their high cost on all of our upcoming flights.
