VA smart purchase in the $300 range
p2990
sg5
VI have been a life long audiophile and luckily for me I have always had careers where I could indulge my interest.  So when I am using a graphic art program at the office a good pair of headphones are worth their weight in gold.  The Bose QuietComfort is most certainly a good pair of headphones with many outstanding features.  It's compact folding design reduces the size of the durable hard shell case making it the perfect size to be tucked away in a briefcase or messenger bag.  The sound quality is superb, of course, and the noise cancellation does a nice job filtering out quite a few annoying background sounds while letting you still be able to hear a ringing phone.  The only nitpick I have is that the plug can be easily partially detached from the headphone causing a mono sound effect, but this is a small complaint.  Although these headphones were calibrated to use with an android device, meaning the inline switch can control the volume, the QuietComfort can be used with ANY and ALL devices but you will have to adjust the volume through the device itself; the inline switch will not work.  If you are like me, most of your listening pleasure is stored on a mobile phone or tablet.  A good pair of headphones can make any high quality MP3 file sound rich and lush, and the Bose QuietComfort is certainly a good pair of headphones by far.  Greatly recommended.
