VSkeptical no more!
p3166
sg5
VBefore I tested these, I thought noise cancelling headphones were just an expensive auditory scam..... I have always wondered what the "noise cancelling" headphone phenomenon was. I mean, don't all over the ear headphones muffle noise while providing sound from the speakers?  Well, yes, but that's not the key to noise cancelling headphones.These Bose noise cancelling headphones are remarkable.  They emit a series of sound waves that neutralizes background noise frequencies.  I tested them in an airport and on a plane.  Without them, there was significant background noise.  When I put these on, it was slightly muffled.  Then I flipped the switch and turned them on.....quiet.  blissful quiet.Not perfectly silent, but SERIOUSLY reduced background noise.  There is a feeling of a little increased pressure caused by the sound waves that cancel.  Some might find it an adjustment, but I didn't have a problem with it.These are expensive, but now I know why people rave about them.  I cannot speak for any other noise cancelling headphones, but these really are impressive.If you can afford it, HIGHLY RECOMMENDED.
