VMy dad and I both purchased the QuietComfort 25. I use mine almost every day and for the price of $300 bucks I take EXTREMELY good care of them! I always fold them back into the case carefully and take care of the cord. After less than 2 months my pair just one day stopped working on the right ear, the side which must be folded to be put back in the case. I was so upset that my dad let me use his while we sent mine in for replacement. After less than another 2 months of use THE EXACT SAME THING happened to my dads pair! Thanks to the warranty Bose has sent us replacements with minimal hassle so I give them 5 stars for their customer service, but the product design (including the storage) of these headphones is absolute garbage. I am a professional musician who listens to everything from classical to rap, and travels on airplanes frequently, I would say that the bottom line noise cancelling and sound quality of the QC is comparable to the Sennheiser PCX450's. Unless Bose improves the build of their product I won't be buying from them again.
