VNot Comfortable at all
p3345
sg5
VThe QC25 headphones are not very comfortable to wear for a long time, as the ear cushion pieces aren't big enough to cover my ears - they are just directly pressing on them. After a while, my ears start to get warm. Also, I think the bridge arc is too narrow, and it makes the headphones very tight. The combination of these 2 problems makes the experience unpleasant. If I were to adjust the arc, the ear cushions would slowly slide away from my ears (again, because they press on the ears, not covering them).I don't know about other happy users of the QC25, but the noise cancelling function is very annoying and uncomfortable. When it's on, (and I have to adjust the ear cushions so they "barely" cover my entire ears; otherwise some noise would still "leak in") it feels like my ears are under water with tremendous pressure.I had tried the QC15, and they certainly didn't feel like this. I cannot recommend these QC25 headphones.
