VExcellent headphones flawed by a cheap carrying case
p3368
sg5
VHaving used these for some time now, I'm delighted with their performance. The difference in perceived noise on flights is remarkable. They seem to cancel noise even more effectively than previous Bose models. They're comfortable on long overseas-length flights. It's hard to imagine how others travel by plane without this technology, although I can understand if the price puts people off. In truth, I can't easily afford them, but I make room in the budget because they're simply essential for travel. I tend to adapt to major shifts in time zones much better than most. I credit part of my resilience to the welcome silence produced by these headphones. One star off for poor functional design of the carrying case. Hard to believe Bose is so unsophisticated or penny-pinching on this high-end product that they couldn't be bothered to figure out what practically every traveler would need. The absence of a small, fifty-cent pouch attached to the lid to store an extra battery is an obvious and hard to justify flaw.
