VGood noise cancelling, ok sound quality
p3380
sg5
VI had the original noise cancelling Bose headphones and really liked those.  On a trip this year the headphones died and never came back to life.  Knowing I had some long flights coming up over the summer I picked up the latest headphones, the QC 25.  The noise cancelling is great on these, as it was on my previous model.  I can't say I noticed any improvement in the noise cancelling but I wasn't looking for any improvement over my last ones as they were already very good.  I'm still not 100% happy with the music sound on these, compared to my original Bose headphones.  The sound is good with regular music but they seem to struggle more with Heavy Metal and Hard Rock.  The base sound seems to be bit off and I find myself having to turn up the volume more to get better sound, then I did with my other Bose headphones.  The QC 25 does seem to have better clarity as I can hear individual instruments more clearly on these than other headphones.  It is just overall, the sound isn't what I was expecting.
