p3391
sg5
VI bought these headphones yesterday and will be returning them today. I am BEYOND disappointed. I have been a loyal Bose consumer for a long time, and these do not measure up to previous products they've produced. Yes, the noise cancelation is impressive, and YES they are comfortable. If those are the only two things that matter to you, then these are perfect for you.However, the sound quality is very tin-y and you have to turn them way up in order to even get a half way decent sound. Once you've turned your volume up to about 80% the sound leakage is ridiculous. Sure, you won't be able to hear the sounds around you, but someone sitting next to you will hear every note and every line of your song... Embarrassing if you feel like entertaining that side of you that has a sudden need to rock out to KE$HA.Minor thing: If the cable isn't in the exact right spot on the headphones, the sound will buzz and cut out.These are not worth the money, sorry to say.
