VThis is not one of those good sounding earphones out there, certainly not for its price. A couple headphones in the $100 range would easily surpass this in terms of sound quality, but who buys a Bose for that?I personally don't use this headphone that much. I usually use a Audio Technica W5000 or a STAX system at home, but none of these would perform in noisy conditions. I also have a couple portable ones like Sennheiser IE80 and Beyerdynamic T5p, but those don't work well in certain circumstances.That's when the Bose comes in. I fly international long flights a lot, and Noise Canceling headphone is a must for me. You just can't find a better headphone to use on flights than this Bose. I previously use a Bose QC15 and QC20i until I lost them. This QC25 just takes it to the next level. It's got similar comfort like the QC15, but the noise canceling is on par with the QC20i.So if you find yourself in noisy condition quite a bit, definitely consider this.
